A Kaduna Chief Magistrates’ Court on Monday, ordered the remand of two men, Musa Yunusa, 32 and Usman Abdullahi, 35, in prison over alleged robbery. The defendants were arraigned on a two-count charge bordering on criminal conspiracy and armed robbery. The Magistrate, Mrs Hajara Dauda, who refused the plea of the defendants,  ordered that they are remanded pending advice from the Director of Public Prosecution (DPP). ALSO READ: EFCC arrests five undergraduates, 12 others for alleged internet fraud “The accused are to be remanded in prison pending the release of the legal advice by the DPP,” she said. Alleged husband killer: Court fixes Oct. 16 for Sanda to… Sanwo-Olu honours police officer who saved robbery victim Customs officers hit schoolchildren with seized vehicle in… Kidnapping: Police kill gang leader terrorising Ogoni… She adjourned the matter until Oct. 24, for mention. Earlier, the prosecutor, Insp Sunday Baba, told the court that one Rabi Yusuf of Ungwan Rimi Kaduna reported the matter at the Gabasawa Police Station Kaduna on Oct. 2. According to Baba, Yunusa and Abdullahi allegedly robbed the complainant of her cell phone valued at N45,500 and N10,000 cash, totalling N55,500 while armed with a locally-made gun. Baba said the offence contravened Sections 59 and 283 of the Penal Code Law of the Kaduna State 2017. NAN SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
